found the firm’s life sciences practice in  he moved to london site of another index office where he continues to reside de rubertis is responsible for all of index ventures’ investments in the life sciences he has served on the boards of directors of many companies including addex therapeutics six adxn cellzome acquired by glaxosmithkline for  million  genmab nasdaq copenhagen gen molecular partners six moln pangenetics acquired by abbott laboratories and parallele bioscience acquired by affymetrix in  de rubertis spearheaded the launch of index ventures’  million life sciences fund in partnership with glaxosmithkline gsk and johnson  johnson jj to invest in earlystage biotechnology companies  de rubertis is the author of several publications in international scientific journals in  de rubertis was named by bioworld as one of  movers and shakers predicted to shape the biotechnology industry over the next two decades  in october  de rubertis was named by xconomy as one of  of “young and proven” biotech venture capitalists de rubertis is a member of the strategic advisory board of the university of geneva external linksedit medicxi website index ventures website francesco de rubertis on twitter referencesedit  jj and gsk join medicxi’s european life sciences push ft february     veni vidi vc pdf university of geneva student magazine november     executive profile bloomberg businessweek may     veni vidi vc pdf university of geneva student magazine november     gsk acquires cellzome  eurobiotechnologynews may     gsk press release glaxosmithkline may     index launches its first life sciences fund m and partnering with glaxo and johnson  johnson techcrunch march     google scholar search francesco de rubertis   the future is here who will shape biotech over the next  years bioworld says… pdf bioworld th anniversary edition    who will survive the biotech vc downturn the young and the proven xconomy october     index ventures partner bio francesco de rubertis  retrieve