microbiology before earning a phd in molecular biology from the university of geneva where he also met his wife sandra henchoz who was a fellow student de rubertis engaged in postdoctoral research in molecular genetics at the whitehead institute at massachusetts institute of technology mit and later earned the chartered financial analyst cfa designation careeredit after his postdoctoral work at mit in  de rubertis moved back to geneva where he joined index ventures and helped cofound the firm’s life sciences practice in  he moved to london site of another index office where he continues to reside de rubertis is responsible for all of index ventures’ investments in the life sciences he has served on the boards of directors of many companies including addex therapeutics six adxn cellzome acquired by glaxosmithkline for  million  genmab nasdaq copenhagen gen molecular partners six moln pangenetics acquired by abbott laboratories and parallele bioscience acquired by affymetrix in  de rubertis spearheaded the launch of index ventures’  million life sciences fund in partnership with glaxosmithkline gsk and johnson  johnson jj to invest in earlystage biotechnology companies  de rubertis is the author of several publications in international scientific journals in  de rubertis was named by bioworld as one of  movers and shakers predicted to shape the biotechnology industry over the next two decades  in october  de rubertis was named by xconomy as one of  of “young and proven” biotech venture capitalists de rubertis is a member of the strategic advisory board of the university of geneva external linksedit medicxi website index ventures website francesco de rubertis on twitter referencesedit  jj and gsk join medicxi’s european life sciences push ft february     veni vidi vc pdf university of geneva student magazine november     executive profile bloomberg businessweek may     veni vidi vc pdf university of geneva student magazine november     gsk acquires cellzome  eurobiotec